ETHICAL PRINCIPLES NOTICE CLAUSE

This software is distributed with a file named PRINCIPLES, which contains
ethical guidelines and goals written by the original authors. These principles
reflect the values the software adheres to. They are not legally binding, but
are provided for users, maintainers, and modifiers for reflection and
transparency.

Verbatim copies of the software must include the original PRINCIPLES file,
unmodified, as part of the distribution.

Modified versions of the software may append their own ethical principles to
the end of the PRINCIPLES file, provided that:

1. The original content remains intact and clearly attributed to the original
   authors.
2. Any added content is clearly marked as belonging to the modified version,
   with the name of the modifier and the date of addition.

Users are not required - but are strongly encouraged - to read the PRINCIPLES file
before using the software. Similarly, user-facing parts of the software are
encouraged to provide a way to display the content of the PRINCIPLES file as
part of the installation process, license agreement, about section, or help
menus.

